content: Single phase: – 32A, 200-240 V AC  Three phase: – 30A, 200-240 V AC (“Δ” - Delta wiring) – 32A, 380-415 V AC (“Y” - Wye wiring) The PDU design also offers some standardization and ease of data center installation planning, which allows the IBM z16 AGZ to easily coexist with other platforms within the data center. Power cables To provide power from the customer supplied PDUs to the different components, the right power cables must ordered as part of the IBM z16 AGZ ordering process. Several options are available depending on the receptacles of the customer provided PDU, the component it powers and system configuration.  Receptacles options – C13: a power cable with a C13 type receptacle is available to provided power to the following IBM z16 AGZ components: • Service Element / Hardware Management Appliance • Network switches • PCIe+ I/O drawers – C19: a power cable with a C19 type receptacle is available to provide power to the following IBM z16 AGZ components: • Service Element /
